If the problem with Czech scientists accused of illegally collecting beetles in India could not be solved, according to Czech Foreign Minister Karel Schwarzenberg, there would be a certain cooling of Czech-Indian relations.
The minister made the remarks in New York after meeting with his Indian counterpart, Pranab Mukherjee, today.
"If this is not resolved, then yes, then there would be a certain cooling," he said after the meeting, which took place on the basis of a Czech initiative.
